Jewellery ERP & Girvi Management Platform

System Architecture Specification v1.0

Document Type: Master Architecture Specification
Version: 1.0
Status: Architecture Baseline
Product: Jewellery ERP & Girvi Management Platform
Technology Stack: Flutter + NestJS + PostgreSQL + Firebase Auth + SQLCipher
Target Market: Jewellery Shops & Girvi Businesses (Maharashtra, India)

⸻

1. Purpose

This document serves as the master architectural source of truth for the Jewellery ERP & Girvi Management Platform.

All future documents including:

* Database Specification
* API Contracts
* Module Specifications
* Screen Specifications
* Development Tasks
* AI Agent Instructions

must conform to this architecture.

⸻

2. Architectural Principles

AP-001 Offline First

Application must remain fully operational without internet.

Supported Offline Operations:

* Customer Creation
* Customer Search
* Girvi Creation
* Girvi Payment
* Girvi Renewal
* Girvi Redemption
* Vault Assignment
* Receipt Printing
* Dashboard Viewing

Cloud connectivity enhances system functionality but is never mandatory for core operations.

⸻

AP-002 Mobile First

Primary Device:

* Android Tablet
* Android Smartphone

Secondary Device:

* iOS

Desktop browser is not a target platform.

⸻

AP-003 Compliance First

All workflows must automatically enforce:

Maharashtra Money Lending Act 2014

* Form 6
* Form 9
* Form 11
* Form 12
* Form 13

RBI 2025/2026

* LTV Rules
* KFS Generation
* Insurance Tracking
* Gold Return Tracking
* Auction Rules
* Pledge Weight Limits

⸻

AP-004 Minimal Typing

Preferred Input Methods:

1. Camera OCR
2. QR Scan
3. Barcode Scan
4. Dropdown
5. Voice (Future)
6. Keyboard (Last Resort)

⸻

AP-005 Auditability

Every critical action must generate immutable audit logs.

⸻

